import { Card, CardContent, CardMedia, Grid, Typography } from '@mui/material'
import React from 'react'
import log from '../images/log.jpg'

const Cards = () => {
  return (
    <Grid container sx={{ background: '#FFFFED', p: 2 }}>
      <Grid item xs={12}>
        <Typography variant="h5" align="center">
          This is the card.
        </Typography>
      </Grid>
      <Grid 
        container 
        item 
        xs={12} 
        spacing={2} 
        justifyContent="center" 
        alignItems="center"
      >
        <Grid item>
          <Card sx={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: 'center', p: 10 }}>
            <CardMedia
              component="img"
              image={log}
              alt="logo"
              sx={{ height: '100px', width: '20px' }}
            />
            <CardContent sx={{ p: 0 }}>
              <Typography variant="body2">Card 1</Typography>
            </CardContent>
          </Card>
        </Grid>
        <Grid item>
          <Card sx={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: 'center', p: 10 }}>
            <CardMedia
              component="img"
              image={log}
              alt="logo"
              sx={{ height: '100px', width: '100px' }}
            />
            <CardContent sx={{ p: 0 }}>
              <Typography variant="body2">Card 2</Typography>
            </CardContent>
          </Card>
        </Grid>
        <Grid item>
          <Card sx={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', alignItems: 'center', p: 10 }}>
            <CardMedia
              component="img"
              image={log}
              alt="logo"
              sx={{ height: '100px', width: '100px' }}
            />
            <CardContent sx={{ p: 0}}>
              <Typography variant="body2">Card 3</Typography>
            </CardContent>
          </Card>
        </Grid>
      </Grid>
    </Grid>
  )
}

export default Cards
